  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, as LLMs are trained on large-scale online corpora, they may inherit social biases and generate outputs misaligned with human values, raising ethical concerns to be addressed [55].To fully harness the potential of LLMs for human-centric AD, we propose the following research directions:• Develop lightweight and efficient LLMs tailored for AD applications with limited computational budgets, e.g., distilling knowledge from large LLMs to smaller models.• Design multi-modal training frameworks that can fuse textual, visual and geographical information to ground LLMs' reasoning in physical AD contexts.",
    "• Introduce safety constraints and ethical guidelines into LLM's training objectives and inference processes to improve the reliability and value alignment of their outputs.",
    "• Leverage LLMs to generate human-understandable explanations of AD behaviors to enhance transparency and user trust.",
    "• Conduct more closed-loop tests of LLM-based AD in realistic simulators and real-world trials to validate their performance in diverse driving scenarios.In conclusion, the integration of LLMs into AD systems marks an exciting frontier in AI and transportation research.",
    "By synergizing the reasoning power of pre-trained models with the learning power of AD agents, this new paradigm holds the promise to achieve human-like or even superhuman vehicle autonomy."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Moreover, as LLMs are trained on large-scale online corpora, they may inherit social biases and generate outputs misaligned with human values, raising ethical concerns to be addressed [55].To fully harness the potential of LLMs for human-centric AD, we propose the following research directions:• Develop lightweight and efficient LLMs tailored for AD applications with limited computational budgets, e.g., distilling knowledge from large LLMs to smaller models.• Design multi-modal training frameworks that can fuse textual, visual and geographical information to ground LLMs' reasoning in physical AD contexts."
